Modified in R4.7.2M.
objects.test: $SNMPTRAPCMD SHE-POTS-ILTF-MIB::shePotsIltfRequestStateChanged SHE-POTS-ILTF-MIB::shePotsIltfRequestStatePortTestState i 0 SHE-POTS-ILTF-MIB::shePotsIltfRequestStateCardTestState i 1 SHE-POTS-ILTF-MIB::shePotsIltfRequestStateTestToneRemainingTime u 0 SHE-POTS-ILTF-MIB::shePotsIltfRequestStateTestModeRemainingTime u 0 SHE-POTS-ILTF-MIB::shePotsIltfRequestStatePortTestModeState i 1 SHE-POTS-ILTF-MIB::shePotsIltfRequestStateLastInvokedTest i 0 SHE-POTS-ILTF-MIB::shePotsIltfRequestStateTestSignalRemainingTime u 0 SHE-POTS-ILTF-MIB::shePotsIltfRequestStateLastInvokedTestSignal i 0

description: The ILTF state of this port.
VALUES
potsIltfNoTestActivity(0) - no test activity.
potsIltfTestRunning(2) - test running.
potsIltfTestToneActive(3) - test tone active.
potsIltfTestSignalActive(6) - test signal active (new in R4.7.2M)
Information about the previously run/requested test activities can be found in
shePotsIltfRequestStateLastReqResultState and testResultState object for each test.
NOTE
Only a single port on each IU card can be under test at any one time.
Ports on different IU cards can be under test at the same time.
Check the corresponding shePotsIltfRequestCardState of the port to be tested for this precondition.
If this precondition is not met, parameter shePotsIltfRequestStateCurrentTestedPort will
deliver the ifIndex of the port on the same IU which is currently under test.
variables.name: SHE-POTS-ILTF-MIB::shePotsIltfRequestStatePortTestState

description: The ILTF status of IU card on which this port is located.
Every port reports the state of ILTF on the card on which it is located, to enable to test
whether a ILTF test request on this port can be accepted.
VALUES
potsIltfNoTestActivity(1) - no test is running on any port of this IU card;
no test tone or test signal or test mode is active;
a test can be started, test tone or test signal or
test mode can be activated on any port of this IU card.
potsIltfTestModeActive(2) - test mode is active on one port of this IU card
(shePotsIltfRequestCurrentTestedPort);
a test can be started or test tone or test signal can
be activated only on shePotsIltfRequestCurrentTestedPort.
potsIltfTestRunning(3) - a test is currently running on one port of this IU
card (shePotsIltfRequestCurrentTestedPort);
no test can be started;
no test tone can be activated;
no test signal can be activated;
test mode may be activated on the port being tested,
if not test mode can be activated only on
shePotsIltfRequestCurrentTestedPort;
potsIltfTestToneActive(4) - test tone is currently active on one port of this IU
card (shePotsIltfRequestCurrentTestedPort);
no test can be started;
no test tone can be activated;
no test signsl can be activated;
test mode may be activated on the port being tested, if not
test mode can be activated only on shePotsIltfRequestCurrentTestedPort;
potsIltfTestSignalActive(5) - test signal is currently active on one port of this IU card
(shePotsIltfRequestCurrentTestedPort)
no test can be started
no test tone can be activated
no test signal can be activated
test mode can be activated on the port being tested, if not
test mode can be activated only on
shePotsIltfRequestCurrentTestedPort;
(new in R4.7.2M).
NOTE
Only a single port on each IU card can be under test at any one time.
Ports on different IU cards can be under test at the same time.
Check the corresponding shePotsIltfRequestCardState for this precondition.
If this precondition is not met, parameter shePotsIltfRequestCurrentPortUnderTest will
deliver the ifIndex of the port on the same IU which is currently under test.
REVISION HISTORY
R4.7.2M: potsIltfTestSignalActive(5) addded.

variables.name: SHE-POTS-ILTF-MIB::shePotsIltfRequestStateTestModeRemainingTime

description: Indicates the state of the test mode for this port.
VALUES
inactive(1) The port is currently not in test mode.
active(2) The port has been placed into test mode.
NOTE:
A port can be optionally placed into 'test mode' that disables the port to allow the
unconditional execution of one or more ILTF tests.
The test mode state of a port can be activated and deactivate through invocation of the
control requests activatePotsIltfTestMode (10) and deactivatePotsIltfTestMode (11)
respectively.
Test mode can be active on one port of an IU card only.
variables.name: SHE-POTS-ILTF-MIB::shePotsIltfRequestStatePortTestModeState

description: The last test invoked on this port.
See shePotsIltfRequestStatePortTestState for current test state.
VALUES
none(0) - No test has been invoked
standardTest(1) - The standard test was the last test invoked on this port
standardShortTest(2) - The short standard test was the last test invoked on this port
additionalTest(3) - The additional test was the last test invoked on this port
selfTest(4) - The self test was the last test invoked on this port
dialToneTest(5) - The dial tone test was the last test invoked on this port.

event.Summary: ILTF standard new test result state is $v1

description: The ILTF result state of the standard test for this port
notTested(0) port has not been tested since reset, no results are valid
testFailed(1) port has been tested, but test has failed, no results are valid
testSucceeded(2) port has been tested successfully; the validity of each individual
result object is indicated by its associated valid object
testFailedStoppedByOperator(3) port was being tested, but the test was stopped by the operator;
no results are valid
testFailedIuCardPulledOut(4) port was in the process of being tested when its IU card was
removed from system; no results are valid
testFailedHwFault(5) port was in the process of being tested, but the test failed as a
result of a HW fault;no results are valid
testFailedTimeout(6) port was being tested, but the test failed as a result of a timeout;
no results are valid
testResultsExpired(7) port was tested (result unknown), but results are no longer available
due to timeout; no results are valid
